Try to Build a Application(Project) Using Gradle and next using Maven

The build.gradle file is the heart of a Gradle project. It defines the build script using Groovy or Kotlin DSL. This script specifies:

Plugins: Add functionality to your project.
Dependencies: Define external libraries or modules needed.
Tasks: Automate specific build operations.
Repositories: Specify where to fetch dependencies from.
Configurations: Customize the build process.